"(1) In a ring of flickering neon, three figures in paint-stained costumes writhed and stumbled, their painted mouths stretched impossibly wide in silent screams. Red nose grease smudged their cheeks like war paint.\n(2) The lead clown’s eyes were white beneath the crimson mask, and as he leapt from trampoline to broken planking, his fingers elongated into skeletal claws that scraped the air. Henry —watching the faces melt, the jokes go flat, the crowd’s laughter curdle into nervous whimpers. Henry Reed.\n(3) A line of people pressed together under a tattered tent, their bodies tense as wires. The lights overhead flickered with a low, irregular hum, syncopated to a heartbeat that seemed to thud from inside the earth. Watched clown performances.\n(4) The clowns’ movements grew less playful; their limbs bent at impossible angles. One dropped suddenly, never landing but sliding through air as though it wasn't real.\n(5) Gasps turned to whines as the painted tears on their faces began to drip, not water but something thick and black. Henry’s own pulse echoed the rhythm of the crowd’s terror.\n(6) He was shivering, unable to remember when he started to feel the cold seep into his bones. The clown nearest the audience reached out a hand, fingers webbed and dripping, but the audience turned their backs, faces scrunched tight, refusing to meet the gaze. St. Patrick's Cathedral. September 13, 2025.\n(7) Behind him, a Ferris wheel creaked with a sound like a dying beast.\n(8) The lights overhead cast long, monstrous shadows that writhed along the ground.\n(9) The painted smile of a clown now loomed ahead of him, split open to reveal rows of glistening, needle-thin teeth"